time required: 30 minutes
---

Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the 
@macaroni{180%grams}.

Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125%grams}. Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} 
(or use a #garlic press{}). Roughly chop the @chives{1%bunch} (use scissors if 
easier).

Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{80%grams}.

In a #large bowl{}, mix in the @red wine vinegar{12%ml}, @sugar{1/2%tsp} and 
@olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing (see pantry for both amounts). Season with 
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Add the tomatoes to macerate and set aside.

When the water is boiling, stir the macaroni into the water and bring back to 
the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back into the pan. Drizzle with oil 
and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, drain the @king prawns{150%grams}. Melt the @butter{20%grams} (see 
pantry for amount) in a large saucepan on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the prawns and stir-fry for ~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw prawns. They're 
> cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Add the grated garlic and the @Central American style spice mix{1%sachet} to 
the prawns. Stir-fry for ~{1%minute}.

Next, stir in the @plain flour{1.5%tbsp} (see pantry for amount). Cook, stirring, 
until it forms a paste, ~{1-2%minutes} - you've made a roux!

Gradually stir in the @water{200%ml} for the sauce (see pantry for amount) and 
the @vegetable stock paste{10%grams}. Bring to the boil, stir and simmer until 
thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in the @creme fraiche{150%grams}.

Add the grated cheese and @Orkney crab meat{100%grams} to the sauce and stir 
until melted, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Mix in the cooked pasta. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Remove from the heat.

Add the @baby leaf mix{50%grams} to the dressing bowl and toss until evenly 
coated.

Share your crab and prawn mac and cheese between your bowls.

Sprinkle the chives on top.

Serve with the salad on the side. Enjoy!